The paper focuses on using Deep Reinforcement Learning for autonomous navigation of UAVs in outdoor environments, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of Deep Learning techniques such as Deep Q-Network and Deep Recurrent Q-Network suggests that the paper also belongs to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of raw image data and feature maps for navigation suggests that the paper also belongs to the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning for control and navigation suggests that the paper also belongs to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
